  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Performing by the Book?\" is set to be published by Leuven University Press in 2024, marking a significant contribution to its field. Although current metrics indicate no citations or online community discussions, the book's future release may foster academic and public engagement as it becomes accessible.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Anticipated for release in 2024, \"Performing by the Book?\" is a forthcoming publication from Leuven University Press. While it currently holds no recorded citations or community discourse on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, its release will likely generate interest and actionable insights in both academic and public spheres.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book\u2019s lack of existing mentions or citations underscores a period of anticipation. Its value may unfold in significant ways as scholars and practitioners begin to engage with its themes, thus allowing it to permeate relevant discourses across various platforms once published.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the absence of high-fidelity social media discussions suggests an opportunity for the authors and publisher to cultivate pre-release engagement strategies. This may include discussions with academic peers, presentations, or informal readings to stimulate interest and positioning within its discipline.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As the narrative progresses toward publication, it is expected that \"Performing by the Book?\" will contribute richly to its academic landscape, potentially inspiring a plethora of engagement avenues that demonstrate its relevance and importance in current and future discourse.</p>",
